    "PU P#0" means "PU object with physical index 0".<br>
    "P#" prefix means "physical index".<br>
    "L#" prefix means "logical index" (the one you want to use in
    get_obj_by_type).<br>
    Use -l or -p to switch from one to the other in lstopo.<br>
    <br>
    Brice<br>
    <br>
